subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Males (
Figs 17–19
) can by distinguished by the combination of tubercles on the carapace surface, an opisthosoma with a chevron pattern and a distinct dorsal posterior sclerotization, a long triangular RTA, and slender, sinuous embolus. Females (
Fig. 16
) can by distinguished by the small anterior hood and the long, forwardly-directed copulatory ducts.
